Based on the data sequences, a phylogenetic tree was developed as shown in Fig. 1
, which describes the relationships between nucleotide sequences of the rC2U-rC3L region in the S1 gene of IBV variants isolated in Taiwan and published data. The deduced amino acid sequences of S1 glycoprotein gene and N gene of passage 74 of IBV 2575/98 and passage 76 of IBV 2296/95 were determined and compared with those of low passage number strains. The results showed that two point mutations caused amino acid substitutions of S1 glycoprotein gene in passage 74 of IBV 2575/98 and six substitutions in passage 76 of IBV 2296/95, but no point mutation was found in N gene after high number of passages (Table 1
).
